G. i. l.—Tbe metro of this Ode is one of three, called after

Asclepiades, a lyric poet of uncertain date. It consiste of single lines dirided thus:

--l-ool-ll-ool-o:

The oseem usually falle on the long syllable after the end of the second foot. There are two exceptione only in Horace, ii. 12. 25, and iv. 8. 17.
